  "writeup": "The Buffalo Bills marked a historic milestone with a ribbon cutting ceremony at the brand-new Highmark Stadium, capping an offseason full of anticipation for the franchise and its fanbase. On the roster front, the Bills waived rookie RB Desmond Reid from injured reserve, while positive injury news emerged for TE Dalton Kincaid as the team prepares for training camp. Debate is heating up in the backfield, with analysts arguing Ty Johnson should serve as RB2 over Ray Davis, and a spring surprise has set up an intriguing camp battle worth watching. Josh Allen continues to dominate off the field as well, leading all NFL players in merchandise sales, while the team added a joint practice session with the Cleveland Browns to its training camp schedule.",
